This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization. It also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses reinforcement learning, which is a sub-field of machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). The paper involves information retrieval as it deals with summarizing documents, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses a policy gradient algorithm, which is a type of optimization algorithm used in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
